00:41:31.730 --> 00:41:33.630
put to a dog or any other animal

00:41:33.630 --> 00:41:36.170
in a comparative psychology approach.

00:41:36.170 --> 00:41:37.310
And there's a lot of research.

00:41:37.310 --> 00:41:39.800
This is not my research
but research of others.

00:41:39.800 --> 00:41:43.080
Looking at really their
physical cognition skills,

00:41:43.080 --> 00:41:45.080
which would be kind of
the problem solving skills

00:41:45.080 --> 00:41:45.913
for the most part,

00:41:45.913 --> 00:41:47.170
and then social cognition skills

00:41:47.170 --> 00:41:51.630
which would be problem solving
that involves individuals.

00:41:51.630 --> 00:41:54.680
And so wolves and dogs put to the same

00:41:54.680 --> 00:41:58.630
physical cognition tasks
performed quite differently,

00:41:58.630 --> 00:42:01.234
with wolves usually surpassing dogs

00:42:01.234 --> 00:42:03.730
if you wanna talk about
who's the better performer.

00:42:03.730 --> 00:42:08.680
So a nice test is a kind
of impossible box task

00:42:08.680 --> 00:42:13.370
where let's say there's a piece of rope

00:42:13.370 --> 00:42:16.830
that's attached to meat
that's secreted inside a box,

00:42:16.830 --> 00:42:20.420
and the animal has to
learn to pull the rope

00:42:20.420 --> 00:42:21.253
and get the meat.

00:42:21.253 --> 00:42:22.450
And both wolves and dogs can do this,

00:42:22.450 --> 00:42:24.530
but then if it's impossible to open,

00:42:24.530 --> 00:42:26.680
they pull it and can't get the box open,

00:42:26.680 --> 00:42:28.730
it's really well fastened,

00:42:28.730 --> 00:42:31.230
the wolf will really go at that task.

00:42:31.230 --> 00:42:32.770
And they will figure out a way

00:42:32.770 --> 00:42:35.510
or they will die trying, essentially,

00:42:35.510 --> 00:42:37.130
to get inside.

00:42:37.130 --> 00:42:38.300
They're intent on it.

00:42:38.300 --> 00:42:42.820
And a dog, alternately,
will go at it a little bit

00:42:42.820 --> 00:42:44.280
and then usually, typically,

00:42:44.280 --> 00:42:48.083
the average dog if there
was such a thing, gives up.

00:42:49.210 --> 00:42:50.990
And then they do something
very interesting,

00:42:50.990 --> 00:42:52.890
which is the social cognitive part.

00:42:52.890 --> 00:42:55.660
Which is to say they look to the person,

00:42:55.660 --> 00:42:58.340
who incidentally is the one almost always

00:42:58.340 --> 00:43:01.510
solving problems for dogs.

00:43:01.510 --> 00:43:05.446
If my dog wants to have food,

00:43:05.446 --> 00:43:08.050
she doesn't go forage for food

00:43:08.050 --> 00:43:09.370
or try to discover it on her own,

00:43:09.370 --> 00:43:11.130
she just comes to me,

00:43:11.130 --> 00:43:14.960
and voila, I am the one who
solves that problem every time.

00:43:14.960 --> 00:43:17.070
And so dogs seem to be very good

00:43:17.070 --> 00:43:21.690
at using us as a kind of
tool to solve any problem.

00:43:21.690 --> 00:43:25.040
But they're sort of failing
the physical cognition test.

00:43:25.040 --> 00:43:27.440
So that's an interesting reason maybe

00:43:27.440 --> 00:43:29.680
some comparative psychology methods,

00:43:29.680 --> 00:43:32.260
and the answers you
traditionally say they give

00:43:32.260 --> 00:43:33.869
don't work as well for dogs.

00:43:33.869 --> 00:43:35.680
They failed the task,

00:43:35.680 --> 00:43:37.630
but they've also really succeeded

00:43:37.630 --> 00:43:39.900
because they've got a much better tool.

00:43:39.900 --> 00:43:41.570
They don't have to go
at that until they die,

00:43:41.570 --> 00:43:43.830
they can just pester the person

00:43:43.830 --> 00:43:46.830
and the person is probably gonna
help them solve the puzzle.

00:43:47.850 --> 00:43:49.610
And so then that's the
social cognition part,

00:43:49.610 --> 00:43:52.100
and they perform much better than wolves.

00:43:52.100 --> 00:43:56.270
One of the methodologies
that has for some reason

00:43:56.270 --> 00:43:57.793
really hit it off,

00:43:59.330 --> 00:44:00.690
and a lot of different researchers

00:44:00.690 --> 00:44:02.540
in this field have studied,

00:44:02.540 --> 00:44:06.750
is like dog's success at
following points, or gaze.

00:44:06.750 --> 00:44:08.810
And they're very good at that,

00:44:08.810 --> 00:44:11.510
much, much better than
wolves for the most part,

00:44:11.510 --> 00:44:13.937
unless wolves have lived among humans,

00:44:13.937 --> 00:44:16.650
and even better than chimps.

00:44:16.650 --> 00:44:18.970
So better than our closest relatives.

00:44:18.970 --> 00:44:20.330
And that seems so automatic, right?

00:44:20.330 --> 00:44:22.980
You point someplace and
the dog kind of knows

00:44:22.980 --> 00:44:23.920
that that's something there.

