00:54:21.960 --> 00:54:25.150
dog might need, or desire, or want,

00:54:25.150 --> 00:54:26.410
or what the dog is telling me.

00:54:26.410 --> 00:54:29.010
So gee, now I understand when the dog is

00:54:29.010 --> 00:54:30.310
trying to get my attention

00:54:31.190 --> 00:54:34.730
for something important that they need.

00:54:34.730 --> 00:54:36.960
The very few things they ask of us, food,

00:54:36.960 --> 00:54:41.410
or going outside, or
interaction, much earlier.

00:54:41.410 --> 00:54:45.840
So I can kind of change the
way a dog gets your attention,

00:54:45.840 --> 00:54:47.210
instead of having to ramp it up

00:54:47.210 --> 00:54:50.340
until they're barking at
you, and annoying you,

00:54:50.340 --> 00:54:51.880
you can see when they just come

00:54:51.880 --> 00:54:55.263
and touch your knee with
their nose as a request,

00:54:56.110 --> 00:54:58.180
and see yeah, you're
communicating with me,

00:54:58.180 --> 00:54:59.580
I'm gonna see what you want.

00:55:00.570 --> 00:55:03.350
That's very satisfying.

00:55:03.350 --> 00:55:05.870
The dog is, if you're seeing
what the dog is saying,

00:55:05.870 --> 00:55:06.960
that's very satisfying.

00:55:06.960 --> 00:55:09.500
And I also am much more appreciative

00:55:09.500 --> 00:55:12.780
of letting my dogs smell the world.

00:55:12.780 --> 00:55:15.920
So we have, I describe in my book,

00:55:15.920 --> 00:55:18.810
the smell walks we take,

00:55:18.810 --> 00:55:20.900
where this whole predefined interaction

00:55:20.900 --> 00:55:22.390
that we have with dogs where we're gonna

00:55:22.390 --> 00:55:23.523
take them for a walk.

00:55:25.030 --> 00:55:25.863
Everyone knows if you're gonna have a dog

00:55:25.863 --> 00:55:27.740
you're have to take them for walks, right?

00:55:27.740 --> 00:55:29.660
And mostly that's about elimination,

00:55:29.660 --> 00:55:30.950
and maybe it's about exercise,

00:55:30.950 --> 00:55:35.950
but lets say you're a dog who's
inside for 20 hours a day,

00:55:37.820 --> 00:55:40.000
with maybe nobody to deal
with for most of that

00:55:40.000 --> 00:55:42.783
because the people you
live with are working.

00:55:44.362 --> 00:55:45.400
What would be great?

00:55:45.400 --> 00:55:46.233
Going for a walk.

00:55:46.233 --> 00:55:47.066
Why?

00:55:47.066 --> 00:55:49.020
Not just so that you can urinate,

00:55:49.020 --> 00:55:51.740
but also to see other dogs
which is very important,

00:55:51.740 --> 00:55:53.830
I think everyone agrees on that.

00:55:53.830 --> 00:55:56.300
But also you can smell
what the world is like.

00:55:56.300 --> 00:56:00.280
So what if we took walks where every time

00:56:00.280 --> 00:56:01.460
they wanted to stop and smell,

00:56:01.460 --> 00:56:04.540
and we're pulling at
their leashes to come on,

00:56:04.540 --> 00:56:06.270
hurry up, we have to take a walk.

00:56:06.270 --> 00:56:08.940
You know, we realize that's their walk.

00:56:08.940 --> 00:56:10.812
They're walking, this is
what the experience is,

00:56:10.812 --> 00:56:14.070
and letting them enjoy that,

00:56:14.070 --> 00:56:15.750
or experience it, whatever it is.

00:56:15.750 --> 00:56:18.020
And I love that now.

00:56:18.020 --> 00:56:20.450
I love seeing my dogs do that.

00:56:20.450 --> 00:56:25.450
And letting them live out
of their noses a little bit.

00:56:25.620 --> 00:56:27.520
So that's, and that's only since really

00:56:27.520 --> 00:56:29.340
I started studying dogs that I did that.

00:56:29.340 --> 00:56:30.810
I didn't know that ahead of time.

00:56:30.810 --> 00:56:34.160
It was only through
reflecting on their capacity

00:56:34.160 --> 00:56:35.330
that I realized I should change

00:56:35.330 --> 00:56:38.340
my way of walking my dog.

00:56:38.340 --> 00:56:40.932
- Well one of the themes in this book,

00:56:40.932 --> 00:56:45.293
