Talk a little about that
because it's clearly a theme

00:57:14.870 --> 00:57:18.100
in the focus that you have on cognition.

00:57:18.100 --> 00:57:18.937
- Yeah, I think you're right.

00:57:18.937 --> 00:57:22.733
And I wouldn't, in cognition
attention is a whole specialty.

00:57:24.040 --> 00:57:25.730
And I never was drawn to that.

00:57:25.730 --> 00:57:29.583
So I think it's a different
type of meaning of attention.

00:57:31.490 --> 00:57:32.532
Now that you mention it,

00:57:32.532 --> 00:57:37.480
what it is is an interest in
looking in a different way

00:57:37.480 --> 00:57:40.330
at something which is familiar.

00:57:40.330 --> 00:57:42.880
You know in some sense that
is a connection between

00:57:43.840 --> 00:57:47.310
my recent writing and my
research in writing about dogs,

00:57:47.310 --> 00:57:49.620
is there is a very familiar thing.

00:57:49.620 --> 00:57:50.700
We already know about it.

00:57:50.700 --> 00:57:52.180
You know maybe some people didn't,

00:57:52.180 --> 00:57:53.760
psychology didn't even think that the dog

00:57:53.760 --> 00:57:54.900
was worth studying cognitively,

00:57:54.900 --> 00:57:55.943
as we already know.

00:57:57.260 --> 00:58:01.270
And now here's an ordinary
block in the city,

00:58:01.270 --> 00:58:05.080
which is a walk I took again
and again for On Looking.

00:58:05.080 --> 00:58:06.280
We already know what's on the walk,

00:58:06.280 --> 00:58:07.620
so we don't need to look.

00:58:07.620 --> 00:58:10.220
And so we've lost a type of attention

00:58:10.220 --> 00:58:15.220
